## interrupt-controller

**Value type:** `<empty>`

The presence of an *interrupt-controller* property defines a node as an interrupt controller node. No value is required — the presence of the property is sufficient.

An interrupt controller is a physical device and will need a driver to handle interrupts routed through it. It may also cascade into another interrupt domain.

```dts
/* arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550.dtsi */
gic: interrupt-controller@17100000 {
    compatible = "arm,gic-v3";
    interrupt-controller;
    #interrupt-cells = <3>;
};
```
